descriptive_summary.title: Edward T. Breathitt speeches

bioghist.head: Biographical note
bioghist.p: Edward T. (Ned) Breathitt Jr. was born in Hopkinsville, Kentucky in 1924. In 1951 he won the first of three consecutive terms in the Kentucky House of Representatives. During Governor Bert Combs' administration (1959-1963) he was Commissioner of Personnel. He beat former Governor Albert Chandler in the 1963 state primary and went on to beat Republican Louie Nunn to become governor. He served as Governor of the Commonwealth of Kentucky from 1963 to 1967.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Edward T. Breathitt speeches (dated 1963-1967; 1 cubic feet; 1 box) comprise speeches given by Edward T. Breathitt during his term as governor of Kentucky. The speeches in the collection are primarily made to conferences, civic groups, the Kentucky legislature, or at the dedication of public works projects.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open to researchers by appointment

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The physical rights to the materials in this collection are held by the University of Kentucky Libraries Special Collections Research Center.
